com.javadude.annotation
Enum Access

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<Access>
      com.javadude.annotation.Access
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Access>
public enum Access
extends java.lang.Enum<Access>

Describes the access level of generated getter and setter methods.

You can specify the access level in the Bean or Property annotations.

In the Bean annotation, the value you specify for reader or writer will be used as the default for all properties defined in the bean.

If the Property annotation, the value you specify for reader or writer will be used as the value for that property only.

Note that there is no "PRIVATE" access value. Because the annotations generate code in a superclass, there would be no way to use the generated getter or setter, so PRIVATE is unnecessary.

Some examples:

@Bean(writer=Access.PROTECTED, reader=Access.NONE, ...)

defines that by default, properties in this bean will be given a PROTECTED setter method and no getter method.

@Bean(...)

defines that by default, all properties will have PUBLIC getters and setters.

@Property(name="x", writer=Access.PROTECTED)

defines a property named "x" with a protected setter. Its getter will default to the access defined in the Bean annotation containing the Property.

See Also:
Bean, Property

Enum Constant Detail

NOT_SPECIFIED

public static final Access NOT_SPECIFIED
Indicates that an access level has not been specified.

It is the default value for readers and writers in the Property annotations.

If unchanged, the readers and writers will be assigned the values specified in the Bean annotation.

YOU SHOULD NEVER USE THIS VALUE WHEN SPECIFYING YOUR ANNOTATIONS.

NONE

public static final Access NONE

Indicates that you do not want a getter or setter. For example:

@Property(name="name", writer = Access.NONE)

would create a read-only property called "name"; it would have a getName() method, but not a setName(String name) method.

PUBLIC

public static final Access PUBLIC

Indicates that you want the reader or writer to be declared PUBLIC.

This is the default value for reader and writer access in the Bean annotation.

PROTECTED

public static final Access PROTECTED
Indicates that you want the reader or writer to be declared PROTECTED.

This is the default value for reader and writer access in the Bean annotation.

PACKAGE

public static final Access PACKAGE
Indicates that you want the reader or writer to be declared without an access modified (package-level access).

This is the default value for reader and writer access in the Bean annotation.
